1) to compile a program javac file.java
2) to run the program java classname
3) create a class which we use to run the program
4) program starts comiling from main function.
6) each line ends with ';'
7) To print to screen System.out.println() or System.out.print()  (difference is new line and same line)
	System.out.printf("******** %s", var_name);  // similar to C
8) defining variable is write the data type and and then declare the variable
9) to read from user  :   import java.util.Scanner;  
	create scanner variable  :   Scanner Scanner_var_name = new Scanner(System.in);
	read                     :   var  = Scanner_var_name.nextDouble();     // we must use nextLine() to read string nextInt for int so on
10) we can use ++ or -- operator both pre and post increment or decrement is possible.
11) +=,-=,*=,/= ..... can be used
12) if, else, else if is same as C, && , || can be used .
13) switch(condition_){
	case val:
		func;
		break;
	.
	.
	.
	.

	default:
		func;
		break;
	}
14) while , do{ .. } while(cond); same as C.
15) To use multiple class just create a class in a different file in same folder.
	class_name classobj = new class_name();   // this classobj is a kind of variable
	now use this obj
16) to create a constructor create a new method and name it same as ur class name.
17) one line if statement condition ? function1() : function2();
18) for loop same as C.
	Enhanced for loop is also supported in java similar to python.
	for(datatype var,array_name){....}
19) To use math functions need not import anything use Math.pow(arg1,arg2)  // any other function
20) Math.ceil(),Math.floor(),Math.max() .... 
21) for Random    :  import java.util.Random;
	// create random obj
	Random rand_obj = new Random();
	rand_obj.nextInt(maxofrange);
22) Array : datatype var[] = new datatype[length_of_array];
	    datatype var[]  = {.....};
23) Array length, array.length
24) Pass array to function same as C
25) Multi dimentional array same as C.
26) if u dont know how many arg u'll send to an arg use :   methodname(datatype...var_name){   }
	// those dots are a part of syntex and the var_name will be an array
